MBOMBELA – Three women and two men were tragically killed in an accident on the N4 near Schoemanskloof. According to Safety and Security spokesman, Joseph Mabuza, the accident happened when a Polo and a Bakkie collided. He said motorists should avoid the area as the road is still closed. ER24 paramedic Kim Habib said they transported two men who were in the Bakkie to hospital with serious injuries. ALSO READ: UPDATE: Police confirm arrest in jogger’s hit and run